<item>
            <title>[PIG-878] Pig is returning too many blocks in the InputSplit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-878</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When SlicerWrapper builds a slice, it currently returns the 3 locations for every block in the file it is slicing, instead of the 3 locations for the block covered by that slice.  This means Pig&apos;s odds of having its maps placed on nodes local to the data goes way down.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
